The 395 people identified in the 2020 census reside in some 190 permanent households (overall there were 681 housing units in Caswell Beach at the time of the census). This population is essentially all white, fairly elderly (median age 63) with more women (55%) than men (45%).  Median household income is $74,219.   None of the population or families were below the [[poverty line]]. While the number of full-time residents is fairly small, in the summer peak population reaches 2,000, mostly family vacationers using rental properties.<ref name="Demographic Profile">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|title=Demographic Profile|website=Census.gov|access-date=January 30, 2019}}</ref>

